# Verify core UI after substantial changes

After completing any of the following, run a `verify-akki-ui` browser pass against the
running dev server (`bun run dev`, served at `http://localhost:5173/pdf-editor`) to
confirm no core functionality regressed — do not consider the work done until this passes:

- An `/improve` run that implements fixes.
- Any "bigger" feature addition or bug fix (anything beyond a one-line/trivial tweak).

Automated suites (`bun run test`, `bun run e2e`) are necessary but NOT sufficient — also
do an interactive browser check.

The executable companion to this rule is the project skill at
`.claude/skills/verify-akki-ui/SKILL.md`, which drives the app with the `agent-browser` CLI
(works for Cursor, Claude Code, Codex, etc.). Follow it for the steps below. The generic
`control-ui` skill (installed from cursor/plugins into `.agents/skills/control-ui`) covers
harness-building in general; `verify-akki-ui` is this repo's tailored checklist.

## What the verify-akki-ui pass must cover

1. Reuse the already-running dev server if present (check the terminals folder); only start
   `bun run dev` if nothing is serving. Confirm `http://localhost:5173/pdf-editor` returns 200.
2. Load `/pdf-editor`, confirm the React root mounts, canvases render, and there is no Vite
   error overlay or console exception.
3. Exercise the core flows: tool switching (Select/Text/etc.), selecting an overlay (inline
   toolbar + Inspector populate), undo/redo, and at least one export path (e.g. CSV).
4. Prefer accessibility refs/labels over coordinate clicks; capture before/after screenshots
   as evidence.
5. Leave the document state restored (undo any test edits) and unlock the browser when done.
6. If the change touched a specific area, additionally smoke-test that area directly.

## Reporting

Summarize what was exercised, attach screenshots, and explicitly state what was NOT covered
(byte-level export correctness and per-fix math stay covered by the test suite).
